<Author>Toxic580
<Content>very good hotel The Westminster City Inn is in a quiet and (I think) safe location. It is about 5/10 minutes from the Pimlico tube station (Victoria line) and about 10/12 minutes from the Westminster tube.It is very handy for the main London sites.The hotel is easy to find (very near to the Tate Britain gallery - next door to a very tall office block. It is very close to the river Thames.We stayed in a suite room (13th floor). Like all rooms, we had superb floor to ceiling windows. We had a Thames view - definitely worth requesting a high floor and Thames view. Superb views throughout the stay. Heard no noise other than the occasional distant emergency services vehicle siren.The suite was of a good size - 6 foot wide bed in the main room, very good sized bathroom (full bath plus double sized shower). The other room was about the size of a European 4 star 'chain' hotel room. The room had a mini bar, Bose dvd/cd/radio plus two flat screen tvs.We had an additional bed for the second 'room'. The room was easily big enough to fit in the bed - the very large settees were also big enough to sleep on if needed.The room and the hotel were immaculately clean throughout.The hotel provides a free cd and dvd library (book your film early in the day to get best choices!).We only used the restaurant for breakfast - as part of the 'deal'. The usual charge for breakfast is 拢13.50 for continental buffet or 拢17.50 for the buffet plus a served hot plate - English breakfast. The range and quality of food was very good indeed. (we are veggies - loads of options).On arrival we (unexpectedly) received a number of hotel vouchers for free cocktails etc - very nice. (but see below). We were also (unexpectedly) offered a late checkout - 4pm.The 'perks' of vouchers, late check out and fruit/water in room seem to be linked to our booking of a suite - although the 'club rooms' may also get the same benefits I think.The hotel seems to have a wide range of deals / rates. We used the hotel website and then phoned to confirm. (we also received a confirmatory email). We confirmed a rate to include VAT (UK tax).Be warned that the hotel website quotes prices without VAT.(this is an additional 17.5%). The only slight 'problem' with the hotel was the checkout I guess. Our initial bill included the charges for the 'complimentary' drinks. It was quite difficult trying to get the hotel to accept that we had received the vouchers on checking in. Eventually these 'free' drinks were not charged for. I think that we perhaps should not have received the vouchers for the two days that we stayed - maybe we should have had them for just one? I still don't know.The bill also showed a charge of 拢100 per room extra per day. We were told that this was because we had a suite (costs an extra 拢100 per day). I showed my email booking confirmation to show the amount in the booking. The hotel honoured the emailed booking amount (ie - not the extra 拢100 per night).To conclude - this is an excellent hotel. I would have absolutely no hesitation in staying here again - or at any other hotel in the chain. If I was booking the hotel in the future I would definitely want the costs and details of my booking very clearly stated in writing in advance. 
