<Content>Return trip to City Inn - still excellent We first stayed at the City Inn in June 2006, and you can read my full review if you scroll back to then :-). We chose it then from recommendations from colleagues at work, and also from Tripadvisor.And it is still excellent! It's still excellent value for money, and is an oasis of peace and calm in the heart of london's Westminster district. Yes, it is a little tucked away in the business district behind Millbank Tower, but this means that you get peace and quiet away from the manic-ness of the West End. but it's still only a 10 minute walk to Pimlico Station (Victoria Line) and 5 minutes down to the Thames (its almost on the side of the Thames). And if you really feel like walking its only a brisk 20 min walk to Buckingham Palace! So you have the best of both worlds - near to stuff, yet peaceful, leafy and pleasant.The hotel itself still provides high levels of customer service, the front desk staff couldn't be more helpful! And we still like the 'City Inn' style rooms above more traditional hotel rooms (more an advert for Habitat and Ikea than dull hotel furniture!!) a fresh and modern approach that its competitors don't seem to have caught onto yet! (which is all the better for City Inn!). We tried some room service this time - i had the home made burger and it truly was a home made beef patty of a burger - huge and really really tasty! And not that overpriced for London either!It's the only place we stay in London now - you are guaranteed a high level of service for the reasonable rates, and peace and quiet (yet close connections to the attractions) and you certainly get a lot more for your money than at bigger hotels who charge more in London. Keep up the good work City Inn! 
