<Content>Fab stay at the City Inn We stayed at the City Inn Westminster for just one night. We booked directly through the hotel website and got an excellent rate of 拢99 including breakfast under the Summer in the City offer. Well, what a fantastic deal! The hotel is well located for Westminster (of course), the West End, the London Eye and Tate Britain. The hotel lobby is spacious and very contemporary. Check in was simple, even though we didn't arrive until about half eleven in the evening. We dropped our bags off in the room and popped to the bar for a quick nightcap. The bar is big and funky, with red and white comfy seats and big glass artworks on the walls. Service is smooth and professional, plus they have an excellent selection of cocktails and whiskies The bedroom was really nice. Simple and plain, with birch furniture (with a nifty drawer containing a kettle and all those beverage essentials, plus Duchy shortbreads) and simple white linen. The bathroom was again simple and plain, well lit, with White Company toiletries and a nice big shower cubicle.Our view (from the floor to ceiling window) was out of the back of the hotel into a quite side street, with Georgian style offices (and a side view of Millbank Tower).The only complaint we had was that the bed was a bit soft. Not a serious problem (and it didn't stop me sleeping like the proverbial log) but we're used to something a bit firmer and not quite so springy.Breakfast the following morning in the City Cafe had tons of choice including lots of continental options (breads, fruit, pastries, cheese, muesli, yoghurt, meats...), full English and a few other cooked options (eggs Benedict, kippers etc) plus lots of tea and coffee. Services was pretty good, though we did have to nag for toast. Checkout was quick and all we had to pay for were our cocktails.I was really, really impressed with the City Inn and were I staying in London again I would definitely stay here again. 
