<Author>dahliaday
<Content>Thank you City Inn! This was the second time my daughter and I have stayed at the City Inn Westminster and I cannot recommend it enough. First of all, it must be the best value in London. Booking through Laterooms, we had a superior double room for 拢88 a night. Where else in London can you get such stylish accommodation with all the super little extras that City Inn offers, at such a price? Luxurious bath robes, DVD/CD player, flat screen TV, attentive 24-hour room service etc. The location, right next to Tate Britain, is superb. And if, like me, you're not that keen on taking the tube, buses to Victoria, Trafalgar Square and the Strand stop almost outside the door. However, the REAL reason for this review is to praise Caryl, operations manager (and her security officer) for the way they handled a rather distressing situation when I thought my wallet and credit cards had been taken while we were at the breakfast buffet. Caryl offered instant support, was reassuring, calm and professional throughout, offering a taxi to the airport next day and waiving aside my concerns about not being able to pay the hotel bill as I had to block both my credit card and cashpoint card. When I susbsequently found my wallet tucked down inside a side pocket, I was obviously relieved but extremely embarrassed about having wasted everyone's time. Caryl and her team were so nice, did not make me feel an absolute idiot (which I really deserved) and went out of their way to make us feel truly comfortable. Which in the end is what a great hotel should do - make their guests feel totally welcome. The management at City Inn Westminster have a splendid team of staff - thank you. 
